  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihoods</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Livelihoods program is a three step approach that begins with group training sessions in basic business principles followed by individual mentoring on learned concepts and direct business improvement suggestions paired with implementation support.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the Livelihoods Program is to provide families affect by the earthquake with a sustainable livelihood. From December 2011 to August 2012 the program expects to provide training, mentoring and support to 48 Small and Medium-sized Enterprises, 120 local youth, and 66 marginalized women members of a handicrafts cooperative.  By doing so the program will promote the creation of over 300 decent employment opportunities. The Livelihoods team will be composed of a mixture of Haitian professionals and international volunteers with experience in business management. This will provide a balance of business processes proven successful in Haiti with innovative practices from North America and Europe.</narrative>
  </description>
